glosses: (for literal or figurative hunger) To be satisfied for the time being after having enough of something desired, to be sated, to be satiated.

examples.text: Adama bir sürü yiyecek getirdik ama hala beklenti içinde, bir türlü gözü doymadı.
examples.translation: We brought the guy a ton of food but he's still in expectation, he's just not satisfied.

etymology: Compound of göz (“eye”) + -ü (possessive suffix) + doymak (“to be full, to be sated”), literally “for one's eye to be full”. Cognate with Turkmen göz doymak, Salar gözi doyğusı, Azerbaijani gözü doymamaq (“to want more of something much desired after enough has been obtained”), Kazakh көзі тою (közı toü), Uyghur [script needed] (köz toymaq).
